  "texts": [
    "However, relying solely on binary classification as a criterion for determining the accuracy of information may not be adequate.",
    "This is because in many cases, the content cannot be strictly categorized as either entirely true or false (Moradi and Chehreghani 2023).",
    "Instead, certain portions of the information are true while others are false.",
    "Hence, considering the option of classifying information into multiple classes or utilizing a credit score system can be a more effective approach.",
    "However, only a limited number of researchers have dedicated their efforts to multiclass classification and as a result, in this setting existing algorithms suffer from relatively low accuracy rates, typically below 50%."
  ],
